repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
I am trying to quantize slow_r50 model, but when i load it, I got this error
```
[ONNXRuntimeError] : 9 : NOT_IMPLEMENTED : Could not find an implementation for ConvInteger(10) node with name 'Conv_59_quant'
```
Code to reproduce
```
class OurModel(LightningModule):
    def __init__(self):
        super(OurModel,self).__init__()
        self.model = torch.hub.load('facebookresearch/pytorchvideo', 'slow_r50', pretrained=False)
    def forward(self,x):
        return self.model(x)

model=OurModel()


input_sample = torch.randn((1,3,30, 256,256))
model.to_onnx('onnx.onnx', input_sample,opset_version=11, export_params=True)

from onnxruntime.quantization import quantize_dynamic, QuantType
model_fp32 = 'onnx/{}.onnx'.format(vital)
model_quant = 'onnx/{}-quantized.onnx'.format(vital)
quantized_model = quantize_dynamic(model_fp32, model_quant)
```
